#. HTML: </p><p> 
#. VAR: Musāvādavagga → paṭha­vi­kha­ṇa­na­sikkhā­padaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:0.4"
msgid "Musāvādavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 10"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:0.5"
msgid "10. Pathavīkhaṇanasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on digging the earth"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-cs-bu-pc10.1, pts-vp-en.2.223, ms2V_321
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā āḷaviyaṃ viharati aggāḷave cetiye."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Āḷavī at the Aggāḷava Shrine."

#. VAR: āḷavakā → āḷavikā (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āḷavakā bhikkhū navakammaṃ karontā pathaviṃ khaṇantipi khaṇāpentipi."
msgstr "At that time the monks at Āḷavī were doing building work. And they dug the earth and got it dug."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:1.3"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:1.4"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā pathaviṃ khaṇissantipi khaṇāpessantipi."
msgstr "“How can the Sakyan ascetics dig the earth and get it dug?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:1.5"
msgid "Ekindriyaṃ samaṇā sakyaputtiyā jīvaṃ viheṭhentī”ti."
msgstr "They are hurting life with one sense faculty.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, pts-vp-pli4.33, ms2V_322
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:1.6"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:1.7"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:1.8"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:1.9"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āḷavakā bhikkhū pathaviṃ khaṇissantipi khaṇāpessantipī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can those monks at Āḷavī dig the earth and get it dug?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:1.10"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, pathaviṃ khaṇathapi khaṇāpethapī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:1.11"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:1.12"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:1.13"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, pathaviṃ khaṇissathapi khaṇāpessathapi."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you dig the earth and get it dug?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:1.14"
msgid "Jīvasaññino hi, moghapurisā, manussā pathaviyā."
msgstr "People regard the earth as conscious."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:1.15"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:1.16"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:1.16a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule">
#. VAR: pathaviṃ → paṭhaviṃ (bj, s1-3)
#. REF: sc3, ms2V_323
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:1.17"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu pathaviṃ khaṇeyya vā khaṇāpeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk digs the earth or get it dug, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc4, pts-cs-bu-pc10.2.1, ms2V_324
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe … ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand— this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc5, ms2V_325
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.1.5"
msgid "Pathavī nāma"
msgstr "The earth:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.1.6"
msgid "dve pathaviyo—"
msgstr "there are two kinds of earth:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.1.7"
msgid "jātā ca pathavī ajātā ca pathavī."
msgstr "productive earth and unproductive earth."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc6, ms2V_326
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.1.8"
msgid "Jātā nāma"
msgstr "Productive earth:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.224
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.1.9"
msgid "pathavī—suddhapaṃsu suddhamattikā appapāsāṇā appasakkharā appakaṭhalā appamarumbā appavālikā, yebhuyyenapaṃsukā, yebhuyyenamattikā."
msgstr "pure soil, pure clay, with few stones, with few pebbles, with few potsherds, with little gravel, with little sand; mostly soil, mostly clay."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.1.10"
msgid "Adaḍḍhāpi vuccati jātā pathavī."
msgstr "If it is unburnt, it is also called “productive earth.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.1.11"
msgid "Yopi paṃsupuñjo vā mattikāpuñjo vā atirekacātumāsaṃ ovaṭṭho, ayampi vuccati jātā pathavī."
msgstr "A pile of soil or a pile of clay that has been rained upon for more than four months, this too is called “productive earth.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, ms2V_327
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.1.12"
msgid "Ajātā nāma"
msgstr "Unproductive earth:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.1.13"
msgid "pathavī—suddhapāsāṇā suddhasakkharā suddhakaṭhalā suddhamarumbā suddhavālikā appapaṃsukā appamattikā, yebhuyyenapāsāṇā, yebhuyyenasakkharā, yebhuyyenakaṭhalā, yebhuyyenamarumbā, yebhuyyenavālikā."
msgstr "just stones, just pebbles, just potsherds, just gravel, just sand, with little soil, with little clay; mostly stones, mostly pebbles, mostly potsherds, mostly gravel, mostly sand."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.1.14"
msgid "Daḍḍhāpi vuccati ajātā pathavī."
msgstr "If it is burnt, it is also called “unproductive earth.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.1.15"
msgid "Yopi paṃsupuñjo vā mattikāpuñjo vā omakacātumāsaṃ ovaṭṭho, ayampi vuccati ajātā pathavī."
msgstr "A pile of soil or a pile of clay that has been rained upon for less than four months, this too is called “unproductive earth.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, ms2V_328
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.1.16"
msgid "Khaṇeyyāti"
msgstr "Digs:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.1.17"
msgid "sayaṃ khaṇati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "if he digs it himself, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms2V_329
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.1.18"
msgid "Khaṇāpeyyāti"
msgstr "Gets dug:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.1.19"
msgid "aññaṃ āṇāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "if he asks another, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.1.20"
msgid "Sakiṃ āṇatto bahukampi khaṇati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If he only asks once, then even if the other digs many times, he commits one offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p></p><p>
#. REF: sc10, pts-cs-bu-pc10.2.2, ms2V_330, ms2V_331
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.2.1"
msgid "Pathaviyā pathavisaññī khaṇati vā khaṇāpeti vā, bhindati vā bhedāpeti vā, dahati vā dahāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is earth, and he perceives it as earth, and he digs it or gets it dug, or he breaks it or gets it broken, or he burns it or gets it burnt, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11, ms2V_332
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.2.2"
msgid "Pathaviyā vematiko khaṇati vā khaṇāpeti vā, bhindati vā bhedāpeti vā, dahati vā dahāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is earth, but he is unsure if it is, and he digs it or gets it dug, or he breaks it or gets it broken, or he burns it or gets it burnt, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12, ms2V_333
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.2.3"
msgid "Pathaviyā apathavisaññī khaṇati vā khaṇāpeti vā, bhindati vā bhedāpeti vā, dahati vā dahāpeti vā, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is earth, but he does not perceive it as earth, and he digs it or gets it dug, or he breaks it or gets it broken, or he burns it or gets it burnt, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.2.4"
msgid "Apathaviyā pathavisaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.2.5"
msgid "Apathaviyā vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.2.6"
msgid "Apathaviyā apathavisaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc14, pts-cs-bu-pc10.2.3, ms2V_334
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.225
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.3.2"
msgid "“imaṃ jāna, imaṃ dehi, imaṃ āhara, iminā attho, imaṃ kappiyaṃ karohī”ti bhaṇati,"
msgstr "if he says, “Consider this/give this/bring this/there’s need for this/make this allowable;”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.3.3"
msgid "asañcicca,"
msgstr "if it is unintentional;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.3.4"
msgid "asatiyā,"
msgstr "if he is not mindful;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.3.5"
msgid "ajānantassa,"
msgstr "if he does not know;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.3.6"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.3.7"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. VAR: Pathavīkhaṇanasikkhāpadaṃ → paṭha­vi­kha­ṇa­na­sikkhā­padaṃ (bj)
#. REF: sc15, ms2V_335,  
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.3.8"
msgid "Pathavīkhaṇanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ."
msgstr "The tenth rule, the training rule on digging the earth, is finished."

#. HTML: </p><p class="endchapter"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.3.9"
msgid "Musāvādavaggo paṭhamo."
msgstr "The first chapter on lying is finished."

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection summary">
#. REF: sc16, ms2V_336
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.3.10"
msgid "Tassuddānaṃ"
msgstr "This is the summary:"

#. HTML: </p><div class="uddana"><p>
#. REF: sc17, ms2V_337
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.3.11"
msgid "Musā omasapesuññaṃ,"
msgstr "Falsely, abusive, and malicious talebearing,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.3.12"
msgid "padaseyyāya ve duve;"
msgstr "memorizing, and two on beds;"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.3.13"
msgid "Aññatra viññunā bhūtā,"
msgstr "Apart from one who understands, true,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc10:2.3.14"
msgid "duṭṭhullāpatti khaṇanāti."
msgstr "Serious offense, digging."
